{"article_id":"BTKdfvyeGIkwnhwC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"John Brennan says","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"lethal targeting of terrorists is carried out legally","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Drone campaign against al Qaeda has been legacy of Brennan as Obama adviser","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"The administration 's top counterterrorism adviser said Thursday","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"he was aware of the CIA 's enhanced interrogation techniques","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"that critics describe as torture","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"while serving as a top official at the agency","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"but did nothing","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"to stop them","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"because he had no oversight role .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"`` I did not take steps","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"to stop the CIA use of those techniques , ''","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"John Brennan told his Senate confirmation hearing .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Brennan was nominated by President Barack Obama","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"to lead the spy agency","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"after Gen. David Petraeus resigned from the job over an extramarital affair .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The issue was controversial in the administration of former President George W. Bush in the aftermath of the September 11 , 2001 , terrorist attacks .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"In answering questions about the techniques ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Brennan acknowledged","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that he knew","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"another part of the agency was carrying out a directive from the Bush administration .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"`` I had awareness","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"that the agency was being asked to do it ;","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"I was aware","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"that the agency was moving ahead on it , ''","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"he told the Senate Intelligence Committee ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"that he was not involved in managing it .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"At the time , Brennan was the CIA 's deputy executive director .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Brennan 's heated Senate hearing","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"MUST WATCH Brennan 's heated Senate hearing 03:22","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"2011 : Brennan briefs on bin Laden raid","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"MUST WATCH 2011 : Brennan briefs on bin Laden raid 03:51","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Who is John Brennan ?","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Who is John Brennan ?","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"02:33","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"On the same issue , Brennan said","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"a committee report on the interrogation techniques contained `` disturbing '' information","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"that raised questions","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"about whether he knew what really happened .","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"The 6,000-page report took six years","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to compile ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"and Brennan said","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"he read the 300-page executive summary before Thursday 's hearing .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"`` Now I have to determine what the truth is , ''","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"`` I do not know what the truth is . ''","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Under persistent questioning by Sen. Carl Levin , D-Michigan , Brennan pledged","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that waterboarding would never be used under his direction ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"but he refused to label it torture .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"On the issue of drone strikes on terrorist targets abroad , Brennan defended the 2011 killing of Yemeni-American Anwar al-Awlaki as part of the war against al Qaeda .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Brennan said","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"al-Awlaki 's involvement in efforts","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"to kill Americans","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"made him a legitimate military target .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Under prodding from committee Chairwoman Sen. Dianne Feinstein , D-California , Brennan confirmed a connection between al-Awlaki and Umar Farouk AbdulMutallab ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"who failed in his attempt","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"to detonate an explosive in his underwear","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"as his Northwest Airlines flight approached Detroit on Christmas Day in 2009 .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"However , Brennan offered no details of the connection ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and noted al-Awlaki 's role as a propagandist for al-Qaeda","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"who fomented anti-American sentiments via the Internet .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"The hearing was temporarily halted at the start","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"when protesters repeatedly interrupted Brennan 's opening statement .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Some waved signs","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"accusing him of war crimes","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"because of the drone attacks .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Feinstein ordered the room cleared of spectators","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"and told security officers to prevent the re-entry of protesters from Code Pink ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"which describes itself as a women-initiated group for peace and social justice .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Brennan is considered to be behind the administration 's dramatic rise in the use of drones against terrorist suspects .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Brennan defended the drone program ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"that Obama `` insisted","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"that any actions","depth":20},{"id":83,"text":"we take","depth":20},{"id":84,"text":"will be legally grounded ,","depth":19},{"id":85,"text":"will be thoroughly anchored in intelligence ,","depth":19},{"id":86,"text":"will have the appropriate review process , approval process","depth":20},{"id":87,"text":"before any action is contemplated ,","depth":21},{"id":88,"text":"including those actions","depth":22},{"id":89,"text":"that might involve the use of lethal force . '' `` My role as the president 's counterterrorism adviser was to help to orchestrate this effort over the past four years","depth":22},{"id":90,"text":"to ensure , again ,","depth":17},{"id":91,"text":"that any actions","depth":18},{"id":92,"text":"we take","depth":18},{"id":93,"text":"fully comport with our law","depth":17},{"id":94,"text":"and meet the standards","depth":17},{"id":95,"text":"that","depth":19},{"id":96,"text":"I think","depth":19},{"id":97,"text":"this committee and the American people expect of us","depth":18},{"id":98,"text":"as far as taking actions","depth":17},{"id":99,"text":"we need","depth":18},{"id":100,"text":"to protect the American people ,","depth":18},{"id":101,"text":"but at the same time ensuring that we do everything possible","depth":16},{"id":102,"text":"before we need to resort to lethal force , ''","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"An unclassified outline of the administration 's policy","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"given last summer to Congress","depth":15},{"id":106,"text":"indicated","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"that the government could use lethal force against an American overseas","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"if the person was a senior operational leader of al Qaeda or one of its affiliates","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"and an attack was imminent .","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"The Senate Intelligence Committee received a classified document on Thursday","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"that seeks to justify the administration 's policy","depth":16},{"id":112,"text":"of targeting Americans overseas via drone attacks ,","depth":16},{"id":113,"text":"a congressional aide told CNN .","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"The document was demanded by lawmakers , mainly Democrats","depth":16},{"id":115,"text":"concerned about secrecy in national security decision making ,","depth":16},{"id":116,"text":"before Brennan 's hearing .","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"It outlines the Justice Department 's legal rationale for the policy","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"of using lethal force against U.S. citizens","depth":16},{"id":119,"text":"fighting on behalf of terrorist groups .","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"According to an official","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"who spoke on the condition","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"of not being identified ,","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"Obama decided to turn over the legal opinion","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"because he believes","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"the scrutiny and debate is healthy .","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"On Thursday , Senate Judiciary Committee Chairman Patrick Leahy , D-Vermont , and Ranking Member Chuck Grassley , R-Iowa , sent a letter to Obama","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"calling on him to share with the committee any legal memos on the targeted killings of Americans abroad .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"`` The deliberate killing of a United States citizen pursuant to a targeted operation","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"authorized or aided by our Government","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"raises significant constitutional and legal concerns","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"that fall squarely within the jurisdiction of the Committee , ''","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"they wrote .","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"One of the questions","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"the committee submitted to Brennan in advance of the hearing","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"asked how it was determined that an individual was associated with al Qaeda","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"and that a threat was imminent .","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"Brennan responded in writing","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"that such decisions were made on a `` case-by-case basis '' in a process","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"involving other agencies .","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"The White House said this week","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"that questions on the matter have been weighed against legal concerns","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"and discussed publicly .","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"The Supreme Court has held","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"that the military may use force against an American","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"who is part of enemy forces .","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"Amnesty International said","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"Congress should grill Brennan on his claim","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"that the Obama administration 's drone strikes are `` conducted in full compliance with the law . ''","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"Brennan 's chances","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"to lead the CIA at the start of Obama 's first term","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"were scuttled by questions about the enhanced interrogations of terrorist suspects .","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"At Thursday 's hearing , Brennan said","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"he had raised objections with colleagues to the enhanced interrogation techniques ,","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"but denied any role","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"in managing or enabling their use .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"Asked if the techniques had yielded intelligence","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"that saved lives ,","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"Brennan did not answer directly .","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"Instead , he repeated his insistence","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"that such techniques would never be used under his watch .","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"Senate lawmakers also asked about Brennan 's role in administration leaks about covert operations ,","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"including a foiled al Qaeda bomb plot in Yemen","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"involving a mole .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"He denied any wrongdoing ,","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"that he had gotten involved","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"only after the leaks became public","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"and that he tried to stem a `` hemorrhaging '' of leaked information in the matter .","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"Brennan acknowledged in his written responses to committee questions","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"that he voluntarily was interviewed by prosecutors about two investigations .","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"in both cases his counsel told him","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"he was being interviewed as a witness , not a target .","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"As CIA director , Brennan would report to James Clapper , the director of national intelligence .","depth":5},{"id":175,"text":"But he would also have a direct path to the president ,","depth":6},{"id":176,"text":"talking to him on the phone or briefing him personally .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":353,"left":0,"right":352,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":352,"left":179,"right":351,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":179,"left":178,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":351,"left":323,"right":350,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":323,"left":204,"right":322,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":191,"right":203,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":188,"right":190,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":185,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":182,"right":184,"